        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(diagnostics-otel): native OTel run attribution via opt-in clientContext",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nMakes the bundled **`diagnostics-otel`** exporter natively attribute a run's OTel spans to a caller-supplied **upstream identity** (e.g. an orchestrator / parent task), end to end, with **no external observability plugin** required.\n\nIt does this in two halves that meet on the trusted diagnostics channel:\n\n1. **Gateway seeds + forwards `clientContext`** (the work in #91762, included here). A gateway `agent` request may attach an opaque, plugin-agnostic `clientContext` bag. It is seeded once onto the run's diagnostic session state and forwarded to **trusted** diagnostic observers on every `session.state` / `message.queued` event — the same shared-state path that already carries `sessionKey`. The bag rides the trusted `privateData` channel, **never** the public event payload, so existing `onDiagnosticEvent` subscribers see the lifecycle events byte-for-byte unchanged.\n2. **The bundled exporter consumes it natively** (new here). `diagnostics-otel` already subscribes to the trusted channel for model/tool content capture (#91256). It now caches `privateData.clientContext` per session from `session.state` / `message.queued`, then stamps those fields as `openclaw.client_context.*` attributes onto the run's `model.call` spans (`started` / `completed` / `error`). No new SDK surface, no out-of-process bridge.\n\n### Why this supersedes #91762\n\n#91762 shipped only the *seam* — the gateway-side forwarding — and framed the consumer as an **out-of-process** observability plugin. This PR keeps that exact gateway work and adds the **in-tree consumer**, so OpenClaw ships a complete, usable native-OTLP attribution feature on its own. Closing #91762 in favor of this.\n\n## What changed\n\n**Gateway / core (unchanged from #91762):**\n- **`src/infra/diagnostic-events.ts`** — `clientContext?` added to `DiagnosticEventPrivateData`; new internal `emitInternalDiagnosticEventWithPrivateData` (public/untrusted emit that still carries `privateData` to trusted listeners). No field added to any public event payload.\n- **`src/infra/diagnostic-client-context.ts`** — bounded, deep-frozen normalizer: deterministic key ordering, prototype-pollution stripping, whole-bag drop on overflow. Size cap measured in **UTF-8 bytes** (`Buffer.byteLength`).\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic.ts`** + **`diagnostic-session-state.ts`** — seeded runs emit via the private path; an unseeded (or reused-with-invalid) run clears the stale bag so it is never misattributed.\n- **`src/gateway/server-methods/agent.ts`** + **`packages/gateway-protocol`** + Swift `GatewayModels` — permissive `clientContext` wire field on the agent request (additive; schema stays `additionalProperties: false`, no protocol version bump).\n- **`packages/sdk`** — `clientContext?` on `AgentRunParams`, forwarded verbatim by `runs.create`.\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/diagnostic-runtime.ts`** baseline — only delta is the `clientContext?` field on the already-exported `DiagnosticEventPrivateData`.\n\n**Exporter (new in this PR):**\n- **`extensions/diagnostics-otel/src/client-context-attributes.ts`** (+test) — pure mapper + bounded per-session LRU cache. Flattens the bag to `openclaw.client_context.*` attributes with deterministic encoding of nested values.\n- **`extensions/diagnostics-otel/src/service.ts`** — remembers `privateData.clientContext` on `session.state` / `message.queued`; resolves and stamps it onto `model.call.*` spans at start and re-resolves on completion/error so attribution lands even if `model.call.started` races ahead of the seed.\n- **`extensions/diagnostics-otel/api.ts`** + **`service.test.ts`** — export + tests asserting clientContext flows onto model.call spans.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal, rebased onto current `main` (Node 22.22.1):\n\n- `tsgo -p tsconfig.core.json` and `-p tsconfig.extensions.json` — both clean.\n- `extensions/diagnostics-otel` `client-context-attributes.test.ts` + `service.test.ts` — **102 pass**.\n- `src/infra/diagnostic-client-context.test.ts`, `diagnostic-events.test.ts`, `src/logging/diagnostic-client-context-events.test.ts`, `packages/gateway-protocol/.../agent.test.ts`, `packages/sdk` `index.test.ts` — pass.\n- `oxlint` + `oxfmt --check` on touched files — clean.\n- `plugin-sdk:api:gen --check` — baseline regenerated against current `main`, check `OK`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** a seeded `clientContext` upstream identity is attributed onto a run's OTel `model.call` spans, delivered over the trusted private diagnostic channel, with the public lifecycle-event contract unchanged.\n\n**Real environment tested:** live OpenClaw gateway driving a real `agent` run on the **native Anthropic transport** (`thinker` → `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6`); a trusted-channel diagnostics subscriber stamped `prov.agent.id`; OTel spans exported to Tempo (TraceQL queried directly).\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** drove a seeded run (`sessionKey agent:thinker:probe-0848151`) whose request carried `clientContext = { schemaVersion: \"agentweave.context.v1\", source: \"conductor-probe\", agentId: \"ConductorProbe-0848151\", agentType: \"main\", taskLabel: \"native-attribution-probe\", paperclip: { runId } }`, then queried Tempo `{ .prov.agent.id =~ \"ConductorProbe.*\" }`.\n\n**Evidence after fix (Tempo, 2026-06-10):**\n\n| trace | rootService | span | `prov.agent.id` |\n|-------|-------------|------|-----------------|\n| `fa187aa716eab5b3…` | `agentweave-proxy` | `llm.claude-opus-4-6` | `ConductorProbe-0848151` |\n| `a97a3b84daa94928…` | `agentweave-proxy` | `openclaw.turn` | (same run, root) |\n\nGateway journal for the run: `started root span … agent: ConductorProbe-0848151` → `model.call.started` → `model.call.completed` (the seeded identity flowed through the trusted channel onto the model-call span, not the default fallback).\n\n**Observed result after fix:** the seeded run's `model.call` span carries the upstream identity; public `session.state` / `message.queued` payloads carried no `clientContext`.\n\n**What was not tested:** (1) The live trace above was produced by an out-of-process subscriber on the *identical* trusted `privateData.clientContext` channel this PR's bundled exporter consumes; the bundled `diagnostics-otel` exporter's own consumption (cache + `openclaw.client_context.*` stamping) is covered by `service.test.ts` unit tests, not separately captured against live Tempo in this run. (2) The codex/OAuth transport path is out of scope (deferred to Mux). (3) CI has not yet run this exact rebased branch end-to-end against live Tempo.\n\n> Out of scope / intentionally excluded: this PR does **not** include two fork-local carries it was developed alongside — the `onModelDiagnosticEvent` plugin-SDK export (separate, #80497) and an env-gated `x-agentweave-session-key` outbound-request header (vendor-specific header name, not upstreamable). Neither is required for the behavior in this PR.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "feat/diagnostics-otel-native-clientContext",
